What\&#039;s on this DVD?

*Starcraft w/Broodwars Expansion and extra maps.
*Warcraft 3 w/Frozen Throne Expansion and MANY bonus maps.
*Age of Mythology w/Titans Expansion
*Unreal Tournament Game of the Year Edition
*Pocket Tanks w/Every Expansion known to mankind.
*Counter-Strike (No STEAM thank god)
*Quake 3 Arena Demo (Only maps that mattered)
*Halo: Combat Evolved w/full dedicated server mappack
*Phantasy Star Online w/schthack server already setup.
*Soldat w/bonus Mario Land map and fully registered.

All of these games will run VERY good on a DVD, requiring no installation (Well unless your DVD drive just blows).  I made this mostly for use in college labs, but it came in handy for some lan parties as well.  Every game I updated as much as possible and patched/cracked then thinstalled with the exception of Halo.  It didn\&#039;t want to thinstall so I did something else (I forget) and it basically installs to a temp folder ensuring there\&#039;s no lag.  Oh yeah, also try putting it all on a flash drive, runs amazing as well.  Even if you run this off the disc, your saved setting will be saved to docs and settings/user/applicationdata/thinstall, in case you were wondering.  Just delete that folder and it\&#039;s like you never played them.  All these games worked fine in computer labs and on library computers that would normally require admin privileges to play on.

Please comment and let me know what you think, thanks! ~Kendog15

AGE OF MYTHOLOGY NOTES
Oh yeah, extra stuff.  Some people (A few XP users) don\&#039;t have MSXML installed
on their computer.  This prevents Age Of Mythology from running so I decided to
include the setup for msxml in the root directory of the CD.  Just launch
msxml.msi to fix this issue.

COUNTERSTRIKE NOTES
Another thing I noticed was for most people counterstrike ask for a serial the
first time they try run a game.  I\&#039;m relatively tired of compiling that .exe so
just use this serial 5RP2E-EPH3K-BR3LG-KMGTE-FN8PY and it should be fine.

PHANTASY STAR ONLINE NOTES
PSO requires a server running, I set it up to work with SCHTHACK\&#039;s sweet private
server (thanks btw a ton schthack).  To create an account just visit <a href="
http://www.schtserv.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://www.schtserv.com/</a> and then you can use that to login in-game.  BTW patch
updates and all that will be saved even if you run the game off the CD.  This is
true for all the games actually and was accomplished by having it all saved in
C:\\Documents and Settings\\user\\Application Data\\Thinstall.  Well with the
exception of Halo.  

Sorry I didn\&#039;t fix those 2 issues, hope this disc still helps everyones lan 
parties.
Later.
